	</item>

	<item>
		<title>Craftsmanship Spotlight: Artisan Behind the Brand</title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
		<p>Every product in our collection tells a story of craftsmanship. This month, we're featuring Maria Rossi, a third-generation leather artisan from Florence, Italy.</p>
		<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

		<!-- wp:paragraph -->
		<p>Maria's workshop has been producing handmade leather goods since 1952. Each piece takes up to 12 hours of hand-stitching using techniques passed down through generations.</p>
		<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Meet Maria Rossi, a third-generation Florentine leather artisan whose hand-stitched pieces take up to 12 hours to create.]]></excerpt:encoded>
